public interface Function<P,R>

In Java, there is no direct support for the declaration of functional types and functional variables. This deficiency is eliminated by the interface Function. The invoke method defines the functionality of a function. This method accepts both separate input parameters and a typed list holding them. The output of invoke is an object of the given return type. Simplified versions of invoke exists suitable for functions with none, one or two input parameters. The invocation of a function is then triggered by simply calling invoke.
